Business Brief -- UJB Financial Corp.:
   Two Planning Proxy Fight
   Demand Stockholder List
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
the investors said that last Wednesday, Chilmark Capital
Partners L.P., Chilmark Capital Corp. Profit Sharing Plan and
Chilmark Offshore Capital Fund Ltd., owners of 4,119,200 UJB
shares, or a 9% stake in the company, demanded a list of
shareholders and other information pertaining to shareholders
from UJB.
   The filing said that the purpose of the demand is to
permit Messrs. Weisman and Cohen to communicate with other
UJB shareholders on matters of mutual interest, including
communicating with shareholders regarding solicitation of
proxies for use at the meeting of UJB shareholders scheduled
for April 20.